.TH "MONGOC_CLIENT_COMMAND_SIMPLE" "3" "2014-05-16" "MongoDB C Driver"
.SH NAME
mongoc_client_command_simple()
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
bool
mongoc_client_command_simple (mongoc_client_t           *client,
                              const char                *db_name,
                              const bson_t              *command,
                              const mongoc_read_prefs_t *read_prefs,
                              bson_t                    *reply,
                              bson_error_t              *error);
.fi
.fi

This is a simplified interface to
.BR mongoc_client_command(3)
\&. It returns the first document from the result cursor into
.B reply
\&.

.B NOTE
.RS
.B reply
is always set, and should be released with
.BR bson_destroy(3)
\&.
.RE

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B client
A
.BR mongoc_client_t
\&.
.LP
.TP
.B db_name
The name of the database to run the command on.
.LP
.TP
.B command
A bson_t containing the command specification.
.LP
.TP
.B read_prefs
A
.BR mongoc_read_prefs_t
\&.
.LP
.TP
.B reply
A location for the resulting document.
.LP
.TP
.B error
An optional location for a
.BR bson_error_t
or
.B NULL
\&.
.LP

.SH "ERRORS"

Errors are propagated via the
.B error
parameter.

.SH "RETURNS"

.B true
if successful; otherwise
.B false
and
.B error
is set.


